## Entity triplanar noise texturing

- What: Noise-textured entity parts now render via object-space triplanar sampling of the shared baked noise canvas, blended by a screen-derivative face normal, instead of the per-face baked-canvas path (Path A) that collapsed to flat color at entity scale. Noise entity parts no longer build `faceTextureGroups` and are drawn with a dedicated triplanar shader; the terrain/obstacle/water per-face path and frequency-pattern entity parts are unchanged.
- Why: At entity scale, per-face noise canvases sized by physical face span collapsed to ~1x1px, producing flat color on cylinders/pyramids/cubes.
- Where: `engine/v1/builder/NewObject.js` — `buildEntityPartGeometryTemplate` sets `template.triplanar` for noise parts and skips face-texture/UV-scaling; `BuildObject` entity-part material sets per-mesh `material.textureScale` when triplanar. `engine/v1/handlers/Render.js` — `createFoggedTextureFragmentShader` gains defaulted `varyings`/`texelComputation` params; new `createEntityTriplanarProgram` + `renderer.entityTriplanarShader`; `collectRenderableMeshes` partitions into `entitiesUv`/`entitiesTriplanar`; `drawMeshList` takes an `options.triplanar` flag and the `drawScene` entity pass draws both lists.

## Image decal opacity (build-time bake)

- What: Image-type texture decals now support an optional authored `opacity` field (0..1, default 1), baked into the decal texture at build time. Values below 1 are composited onto a straight-alpha 2D canvas via `globalAlpha`; opacity >= 1 keeps the raw bitmap fast path. Shape decals and the render/tint path are untouched.
- Why: Image decals previously had no opacity control (raw bitmap used directly, render tint forced to opaque), while shape decals already supported it via `color.a`.
- Where: `engine/v1/core/normalize.js` — `normalizeCustomTextures` image branch reads/clamps `opacity` off the raw pre-schema entry and assigns `entry.opacity`. `engine/v1/builder/NewTexture.js` — `collectCustomTextures` carries `opacity` into the image usage entry; new `bakeImageDecalOpacity` helper; `createTextureRegistry` custom-texture loop bakes opacity for image decals.

## Curved-surface decal conforming

- What: Decals (custom textures) now conform to the underlying primitive surface (sphere/cylinder/capsule, flat fallback otherwise) instead of floating on a single flat quad tangent to the bounding-box face. The flat decal quad is now a tessellated grid, projected onto the surface in a dedicated decal vertex shader after dynamic per-frame placement.
- Why: On curved geometry (e.g. Carl's rounded head) the old flat 4-vertex quad floated off the surface. Conforming happens in the vertex shader so the runtime decal animation channels (transform/tint/swap) stay dynamic and are not baked.
- Where: `engine/v1/handlers/Render.js` — new `createDecalProgram` + `shapeEnum` + `DECAL_SHAPE_*` enum and `renderer.decalShader` registration; `ensureDecalQuadBuffer` now builds an N×N tessellated grid with `indexCount`; `buildDecalModelMatrix` split into `buildDecalPlacementMatrix` (part-local only); `drawDecalPass` uses the decal shader, passes `u_placement`/`u_partWorld`/`u_shape`/`u_halfExtents`. GLSL `projectToSurface` mirrors `buildSphere`/`buildCylinder`/`buildCapsule` in `engine/v1/builder/NewObject.js`.

## Decal/scatter render-pass cleanup

- What: Audit-driven cleanup of the decal-conforming code: shape-enum constants renamed to lowerCamelCase, the duplicated 4×4 matrix multiply consolidated into a shared `MultiplyMatrix4` export, the static decal face-rotation table hoisted to module scope, and the decal + scatter passes now reuse `configureTexturedMeshPass` for pass-level uniforms. `drawDecalPass` restructured so mesh-level uniforms (`u_partWorld`/`u_shape`/`u_halfExtents`/sampler slot) are set once per mesh while placement/tint/texture-bind remain per-decal.
- Why: Remove duplication and per-decal redundant uniform writes flagged by DRYAD, and bring constant naming into line with CASING rules.
- Where: `engine/v1/math/Matrix.js` — `multiplyMatrix4` exported as `MultiplyMatrix4`. `engine/v1/handlers/Render.js` — `shapeEnum`/`decalShape*` constants, module-scope `decalFaceRotations`, `buildDecalPlacementMatrix`, `drawDecalPass`, and the scatter pass in `drawScene`.
